{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-19",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_19_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 19 - The Russian's Hand",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 4,
  "page_total": 10,
  "page_start_sec": 742.656,
  "page_end_sec": 983.36,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.671,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 742.656,
      "end": 744.06,
      "text": "\"'That's fine,' Spade said.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 744.61,
      "end": 747.1,
      "text": "If any slip-up makes it necessary for"
    },
    {
      "start": 747.1,
      "end": 748.58,
      "text": "us to try him for Jacoby's murder,"
    },
    {
      "start": 748.92,
      "end": 750.84,
      "text": "we can also hang an arson charge on him."
    },
    {
      "start": 751.66,
      "end": 752.04,
      "text": "All right.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 752.48,
      "end": 752.86,
      "text": "Now,"
    },
    {
      "start": 753.08,
      "end": 753.86,
      "text": "about the shooting."
    },
    {
      "start": 754.84,
      "end": 755.32,
      "text": "Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 755.38,
      "end": 755.6,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 756.16,
      "end": 759.12,
      "text": "we dashed all around town all day trying to find them,"
    },
    {
      "start": 759.68,
      "end": 761.3,
      "text": "and we found them late this afternoon."
    },
    {
      "start": 761.88,
      "end": 764.46,
      "text": "We weren't sure at first that we had found them."
    },
    {
      "start": 765.4,
      "end": 768.16,
      "text": "All we were sure of was that we had found Mr.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 768.3,
      "end": 770.18,
      "text": "Shaughnessy's apartment on California Street."
    },
    {
      "start": 770.81,
      "end": 774.16,
      "text": "But when we listened at the door we heard them moving inside,"
    },
    {
      "start": 774.54,
      "end": 776.26,
      "text": "so we were pretty confident"
    },
    {
      "start": 776.26,
      "end": 776.94,
      "text": "we had them,"
    },
    {
      "start": 777.08,
      "end": 778.04,
      "text": "and rang the bell."
    },
    {
      "start": 778.74,
      "end": 780.9,
      "text": "When she asked us who we were and we told her,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 781.0,
      "end": 782.74,
      "text": "we heard a window going up."
    },
    {
      "start": 783.72,
      "end": 784.84,
      "text": "We knew what that meant,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 784.92,
      "end": 785.32,
      "text": "of course,"
    },
    {
      "start": 785.44,
      "end": 788.92,
      "text": "so Willimer hurried downstairs as fast as he could and"
    },
    {
      "start": 788.96,
      "end": 791.54,
      "text": "around to the back of the building to cover the fire-escape."
    },
    {
      "start": 792.736,
      "end": 794.92,
      "text": "And when he turned into the alley he ran right",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 794.92,
      "end": 797.5,
      "text": "plump smack into Jacoby running away with"
    },
    {
      "start": 797.5,
      "end": 798.72,
      "text": "the falcon under his arm."
    },
    {
      "start": 800.02,
      "end": 802.02,
      "text": "That was a difficult situation to handle,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 802.12,
      "end": 804.74,
      "text": "but Wilmer did every bit as well as he could."
    },
    {
      "start": 805.78,
      "end": 807.64,
      "text": "He shot Jacobi more than once,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 808.32,
      "end": 811.98,
      "text": "but Jacobi was too tough either to fall down or drop the falcon,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 812.72,
      "end": 815.4,
      "text": "and he was too close for Wilmer to keep out of his way.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 815.74,
      "end": 818.02,
      "text": "He knocked Wilmer down and ran."
    },
    {
      "start": 818.82,
      "end": 820.4,
      "text": "And this was in broad daylight,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 820.52,
      "end": 821.02,
      "text": "you understand,"
    },
    {
      "start": 821.18,
      "end": 821.86,
      "text": "in the afternoon."
    },
    {
      "start": 822.848,
      "end": 825.02,
      "text": "And when Wilmer got up he could see a",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 825.02,
      "end": 826.64,
      "text": "policeman coming up from the block below."
    },
    {
      "start": 827.64,
      "end": 829.18,
      "text": "So he had to give it up.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 829.728,
      "end": 832.94,
      "text": "He dodged into the open back of the building next to the coronet,"
    },
    {
      "start": 833.26,
      "end": 834.08,
      "text": "into the street,"
    },
    {
      "start": 834.22,
      "end": 835.5,
      "text": "and then in to join us,"
    },
    {
      "start": 836.04,
      "end": 838.44,
      "text": "and very fortunate he was to make it safely."
    },
    {
      "start": 839.48,
      "end": 839.88,
      "text": "Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 839.96,
      "end": 840.18,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 840.34,
      "end": 842.0,
      "text": "there we were stumped again."
    },
    {
      "start": 843.4,
      "end": 845.82,
      "text": "Miss O'Shaughnessy had opened the door for Cairo and",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 845.96,
      "end": 848.8,
      "text": "me after she had seen Jacoby safely out the window,"
    },
    {
      "start": 848.96,
      "end": 852.096,
      "text": "and she—he smiled at a memory—we"
    },
    {
      "start": 852.73,
      "end": 853.18,
      "text": "persuaded,"
    },
    {
      "start": 853.5,
      "end": 854.48,
      "text": "that is the word,"
    },
    {
      "start": 854.54,
      "end": 854.7,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 855.32,
      "end": 856.82,
      "text": "her to tell us that she had told"
    },
    {
      "start": 856.86,
      "end": 858.58,
      "text": "Jacobi to take the falcon to you."
    },
    {
      "start": 859.74,
      "end": 861.34,
      "text": "It looked very unlikely that he'd",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 861.34,
      "end": 862.04,
      "text": "live to get there,"
    },
    {
      "start": 862.29,
      "end": 864.56,
      "text": "even if he wasn't picked up by the police on his"
    },
    {
      "start": 864.56,
      "end": 864.76,
      "text": "way,"
    },
    {
      "start": 864.92,
      "end": 866.92,
      "text": "but that was the only chance we had,"
    },
    {
      "start": 867.08,
      "end": 867.26,
      "text": "sir."
    },
    {
      "start": 868.28,
      "end": 868.62,
      "text": "And so,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 868.82,
      "end": 869.6,
      "text": "once more,"
    },
    {
      "start": 869.8,
      "end": 870.2,
      "text": "we"
    },
    {
      "start": 870.44,
      "end": 873.08,
      "text": "persuaded Miss O'Shaughnessy to give us a little assistance."
    },
    {
      "start": 874.54,
      "end": 874.86,
      "text": "We had",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 874.94,
      "end": 878.1,
      "text": "her phone you in an attempt to draw you away from your office before"
    },
    {
      "start": 878.18,
      "end": 879.08,
      "text": "Jacobi got there,"
    },
    {
      "start": 879.26,
      "end": 880.86,
      "text": "and we sent Wilmer after him."
    },
    {
      "start": 881.32,
      "end": 882.08,
      "text": "Unfortunately,"
    },
    {
      "start": 882.78,
      "end": 884.62,
      "text": "it had taken us too long to decide,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 884.88,
      "end": 887.68,
      "text": "and too long to persuade Miss O'Shaughnessy to—"
    },
    {
      "start": 888.58,
      "end": 891.24,
      "text": "The boy on the sofa groaned and rolled over on his side.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 891.6,
      "end": 894.26,
      "text": "His eyes opened and closed several times."
    },
    {
      "start": 894.71,
      "end": 898.12,
      "text": "The girl stood up and moved into the angle of table and wall again."
    },
    {
      "start": 899.424,
      "end": 902.62,
      "text": "\"'To cooperate with us,' Gutman concluded hurriedly.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 903.36,
      "end": 906.6,
      "text": "\"'And so you had the Falcon before we could reach you.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 907.69,
      "end": 910.12,
      "text": "The boy put one foot down on the floor,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 910.3,
      "end": 911.84,
      "text": "raised himself on an elbow,"
    },
    {
      "start": 912.08,
      "end": 913.36,
      "text": "opened his eyes wide,"
    },
    {
      "start": 913.7,
      "end": 914.94,
      "text": "put the other foot down,"
    },
    {
      "start": 915.12,
      "end": 916.52,
      "text": "sat up and looked around."
    },
    {
      "start": 917.76,
      "end": 919.42,
      "text": "When his eyes focused on Spade,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 919.54,
      "end": 920.19,
      "text": "bewilderment"
    },
    {
      "start": 920.3,
      "end": 920.94,
      "text": "went out of them."
    },
    {
      "start": 922.368,
      "end": 924.66,
      "text": "Kyril left the armchair and went over to the boy.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 925.48,
      "end": 926.8,
      "text": "He put his arm on the boy's shoulder",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 927.02,
      "end": 928.32,
      "text": "and started to say something."
    },
    {
      "start": 928.86,
      "end": 931.02,
      "text": "The boy rose to his feet quickly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 931.37,
      "end": 932.56,
      "text": "shaking the arm off his"
    },
    {
      "start": 932.58,
      "end": 932.78,
      "text": "shoulder."
    },
    {
      "start": 933.31,
      "end": 936.62,
      "text": "He glanced around the room once and then fixed his eyes on"
    },
    {
      "start": 936.68,
      "end": 937.22,
      "text": "Spade again."
    },
    {
      "start": 938.6,
      "end": 939.9,
      "text": "His face was set hard,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 940.46,
      "end": 942.48,
      "text": "and he held his body so tense that"
    },
    {
      "start": 942.56,
      "end": 944.22,
      "text": "it seemed drawn in and shrunken."
    },
    {
      "start": 945.27,
      "end": 945.72,
      "text": "Spade,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 945.88,
      "end": 947.08,
      "text": "sitting on a corner of the"
    },
    {
      "start": 947.3,
      "end": 947.42,
      "text": "table,"
    },
    {
      "start": 947.5,
      "end": 948.94,
      "text": "swinging his legs carelessly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 949.0,
      "end": 949.3,
      "text": "said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 950.44,
      "end": 950.88,
      "text": "\"'Now listen,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 951.0,
      "end": 951.22,
      "text": "kid,"
    },
    {
      "start": 951.39,
      "end": 953.82,
      "text": "if you come over here and start cutting up I'm going"
    },
    {
      "start": 953.82,
      "end": 954.78,
      "text": "to kick you in the face."
    },
    {
      "start": 955.776,
      "end": 958.04,
      "text": "Sit down and shut up and behave and you'll last",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 958.2,
      "end": 958.66,
      "text": "longer.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 960.1,
      "end": 961.12,
      "text": "The boy looked at Gutman.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 962.496,
      "end": 964.56,
      "text": "Gutman smiled benignly at him and said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 965.09,
      "end": 965.74,
      "text": "\"'Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 965.74,
      "end": 966.04,
      "text": "Wilmer,"
    },
    {
      "start": 966.25,
      "end": 968.08,
      "text": "I'm sorry to lose you indeed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 968.48,
      "end": 969.84,
      "text": "and I want you to know"
    },
    {
      "start": 969.84,
      "end": 972.92,
      "text": "that I couldn't be any fonder of you if you were my own son."
    },
    {
      "start": 973.34,
      "end": 974.06,
      "text": "But,"
    },
    {
      "start": 974.14,
      "end": 974.66,
      "text": "well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 974.66,
      "end": 975.18,
      "text": "by gad,"
    },
    {
      "start": 975.36,
      "end": 978.4,
      "text": "if you lose a son it's possible to get another,"
    },
    {
      "start": 978.58,
      "end": 979.74,
      "text": "and there's only"
    },
    {
      "start": 979.9,
      "end": 981.44,
      "text": "one Maltese falcon.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 982.496,
      "end": 983.36,
      "text": "Spade laughed.",
      "para_break": true
    }
  ]
}